&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assistant Practice Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northenden Group Practice&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced, enthusiastic and self-motivated Assistant Practice Manager to join our friendly and professional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With 10,100 patients, our team consists of 5 GP Partners, 6 Salaried GPs, 1 Assistant Nurse practitioner, 3 Practice Nurses, 2 HCA , 3 Secretaries and an experienced and supportive team of receptionists/administrators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will assist the Practice Manager in ensuring the smooth, efficient and safe running of the practice. Ideally applicants will possess:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good people management skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and IT skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General practice experience in a supervisory role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work within a team and use own initiative.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferably experience of general practice IT systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary dependant on experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits to the practice can be arranged, please email allison.hey@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: Friday6thNovember 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
